Machakos county became the hotbed of love over the weekend after the seventh edition of Country Roads Macha hosted the best of the best country music performances. Enthusiasts thronged the Machakos Peoplesâ€™ Park looking dapper in cowboy hats. To open the stage was Burundian sensation Hope, and a later rendition of country music by Steve Rogers. Jeff Koinange, Kareh B, Kidum and Prof Hammo took the night away, taking the event that began at four in the evening up to four in the morning.